          <p>Portugal's soul music — melancholic, passionate, and deeply beautiful. We'll listen and discuss in class.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="why-item">
        <span class="why-item__icon"><i data-lucide="grid-2x2"></i></span>
        <div>
          <h3>Azulejos</h3>
          <p>The iconic blue-and-white ceramic tiles that tell Portugal's stories on every building and wall.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="why-item">
        <span class="why-item__icon"><i data-lucide="cookie"></i></span>
        <div>
          <h3>Pastéis de Nata</h3>
          <p>Custard tarts that are a national treasure. Learning to order them properly may be your first great victory in Portuguese.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="why-item">
        <span class="why-item__icon"><i data-lucide="fish"></i></span>
        <div>
          <h3>Bacalhau</h3>
          <p>Salt cod — prepared 365 different ways, one for each day of the year. A true symbol of Portuguese identity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
